        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> What some people are failing to realize is that Dire Charm isn't something that Verant just "handed out".  If you have it, you worked pretty hard for it.  If it gets nerfed, there will be quite an uproar; particularly from necros who can only do undead and druids who can only do animals.</P><P>They seem to think that having a Dire pet is just as simple as having a normal pet - which is not the case.  There are many downsides to a Dire pet (particularly for necros), not the least of which is going LD and losing *it* and anything *given* to it, and not being able to get another for an hour.  I've also heard rumors of lag causing it to break (hasn't happened to me).  </P><P>I think the previous poster was correct tho - rather than people going "Hey that chanter/necro/druid kicks ASS with a Dire pet, we want him on this Raid!!!", they are saying "Hey what the fuck, he outdamages me, unfair thx, nerf him."  It's lame.</P><P>Jeddia Seltarinéo<BR>Human Warlock of The Prince of Hate - Quellious<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51060" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51060</a><BR><img src="http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/~jeddia/shot.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
