e Charm that the pet would break and attack me.</P><P>Does not happen often but I have seen it happen before.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Magicians pay a very heavy penalty to have the greatest permanent pets.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>When the hell are you mages going to remember that you also have the second/third [depending upon level] DD/AoEs, the best damage shields and the only class with the ability to summon a living player to your side?!?  You are MORE then just the sum of our pets.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Those of you who don't see this are selfish children.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Nice that you can be objective when having discussions.  Funny but I did not notice alot of Mages commenting upon how wrong it was that the Mages Epic pet did 10 TIMES the damage of the Necromancer pet in that little logged fight.  So if you think Dire Charm is over powered purily based upon damage output, then what about that epic pet?</P><P>Dire Charm is a "fun" skill, sure it is usefull for xping but at the level Dire Charm is usable who is really has problems getting xps?  At that level the game is about RAIDS and there are less then a handfull of raid zones where one can Dire Charm.  Ever seen a Dire Charmable mob in ToV?  I have not but I have seen epic pets.</P><P>Bril</P><P></P><P></P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
